This project involves the information about diamonds right from their colour to the fime edge cutting d it has , here there is exploratory data analysis performed on the data from kaggle and the various aspects are highlighted in the following . The data is available on the link : https://www.kaggle.com/shivam2503/diamonds

Few observations from the above plot

  • x,y, and z have a very strong relation with price but surprisingly depth (which comes from x,y, and z) doesn't has a significant relation with price.
  • Carat has a strong relation with price
  • Table doesn't have a significant relation with price or any other variable as well ( We can try dropping that when making the model)

In [122]:
from sklearn.metrics import mean_absolute_error,r2_score,mean_squared_error
In [123]:
# create a function to evaluate the model on different levels:
def show_scores(model):
    train_preds = model.predict(x_train)
    test_preds = model.predict(x_test)
    scores = {'Train MAE':mean_absolute_error(y_train,train_preds),
             'test MAE':mean_absolute_error(y_test,test_preds),
             'Train MSE':mean_squared_error(y_train,train_preds),
             'test MSE':mean_squared_error(y_test,test_preds),
             'Train r2':r2_score(y_train,train_preds),
             'test r2':r2_score(y_test,test_preds)}
    return scores
